snippet.title: Predator: Badlands | Final Trailer
snippet.description:
Watch the new trailer for Predator: Badlands. Experience the film only in theaters and IMAX November 7.

Set in the future on a deadly remote planet, “Badlands” follows a young Predator outcast (played by newcomer Dimitrius Schuster-Koloamatangi) who finds an unlikely ally in Thia (Emmy and Golden Globe nominee Elle Fanning) as he embarks on a treacherous journey in search of the ultimate adversary. Produced by John Davis, Dan Trachtenberg, Marc Toberoff, Ben Rosenblatt and Brent O’Connor, “Predator: Badlands” opens exclusively in movie theaters on November 7 in IMAX, Dolby Cinema, RealD (3D), Cinemark XD, 4DX, ScreenX and premium screens everywhere.

snippet.title: Medusa (2025) - First Trailer | Florence Pugh, Henry Cavill, Jenna Ortega
snippet.description:
#medusa #florencepugh #jennaortega

Florence Pugh and Jenna Ortega rumored for mythic Medusa reboot.

Editing, VFX, SFX, Thumbnail by @KHStudio please subscribe:
✅ YouTube: https://bit.ly/KHstudio

🎥 Attention viewers!

Please note that this video is a concept trailer created solely for artistic and entertainment purposes. I have meticulously incorporated various effects, sound design, AI technologies (Google Veo 3), movie analytics, and other elements to bring my vision to life. Its purpose is purely artistic, aiming to entertain and engage with the YouTube community. My goal is to showcase my creativity and storytelling skills through this trailer. Thank you for your support, and let's dive into the world of imagination! 🍿

🐍 Medusa

Speculation envisions a character-driven reimagining where Florence Pugh’s Medusa is less monster than misread legend—exiled, powerful, and forced to decide whether vengeance or mercy defines her name. Jenna Ortega is rumored as an Oracle who foresees a war born from fear, not fate, and must choose between truth and survival.

Industry whispers hint at tactile, myth-grounded worldbuilding: windswept islands, crumbling temples, and practical creature effects enhanced with delicate, uncanny details. Themes of gaze, control, and transformation could drive the story, inviting audiences to question who gets to tell a legend—and why.

No confirmations yet, but fans picture a finale that shifts the power of the myth itself, with choices that echo beyond the battlefield and a tone that balances epic spectacle with intimate stakes.

Feel free to express your thoughts on this exciting project by leaving a comment below.

snippet.description:
Support Journey to the Quest becoming a real show! 
https://www.kickstarter.com/projects/totu/journey-to-the-quest-an-animated-pilot

We're finally here! After months and months of waiting and even more months of work we are ready to finally premiere our Kickstarter! This will be the BEST PLACE to get merch themed around the characters you love. Our little show has grown and evolved to the point that if we want to keep growing it, we will need your help. We want to make a studio quality pilot, which means proper fluid animation. Once we have the episode, we want to release it to all of you and take it to studios to hopefully get a proper show made! In the meantime, we will still be releasing episodes about your favorite Warlock, Bard, Rogue, Ranger, and Barbarian. These adventurers will be gracing Instagram, Tik-Tok, and YouTube for the foreseeable future. We just want to make more and expand what we are able to do. If you can support us, please do, and if you can't afford it, then just make sure to engage with all our videos until we're done. Thank you all so much, and I can't wait to see how far we can go.
